lt\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_TI1rKW6eKZX0xJrUtoUGaVIW|fc_0b9534823d32c12b016a02360885bc819db2ca765bcdb8e9ff\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"541:        destination.setBytes(destinationIndex, this, index, length);\\n637:    public void setByte(int index, int value)\\n640:        setByteUnchecked(index, value);\\n643:    void setByteUnchecked(int index, int value)\\n736:    public void setBytes(int index, Slice source)\\n738:        setBytes(index, source, 0, source.length());\\n754:    public void setBytes(int index, Slice source, int sourceIndex, int length)\\n769:    public void setBytes(int index, byte[] source)\\n771:        setBytes(index, source, 0, source.length);\\n784:    public void setBytes(int index, byte[] source, int sourceIndex, int length)\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778529801157}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/io.airlift:slice:0.36/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-11T20-05-14-042553Z.log:1752:[thinking] I’m thinking about how the ClassLoader.loadClass and getDeclaredConstructor might require `--add-opens` for the native image. It seems the generated metadata includes Field Buffer.address, which is good. On a positive note, there’s no direct reflection in my tests. I’m also considering the potential test package name io_airlift, which sounds solid. Next steps involve writing the file, removing the placeholder, and editing the build. It’s got quite a bit to tackle!\nhuman-intervention-logs/io.airlift:slice:0.36/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-11T20-05-14-042553Z.log:1756:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/io.airlift/slice/0.36/src/test/java/io_airlift/slice/JvmUtilsTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage io_airlift.slice;\\n\\nimport io.airlift.slice.Slice;\\nimport io.airlift.slice.Slices;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class JvmUtilsTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void wrappedBufferReadsAndWritesDirectBufferVisibleRegion() {\\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(8);\\n        for (int index = 0; index < buffer.capacity(); index++) {\\n            buffer.put(index, (byte) (index + 1));\\n        }\\n        buffer.position(2);\\n        buffer.limit(6);\\n\\n        Slice slice = Slices.wrappedBuffer(buffer);\\n\\n        assertThat(slice.length()).isEqualTo(4);\\n        assertThat(slice.getBase()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(slice.getAddress()).isPositive();\\n        assertThat(slice.getByte(0)).isEqualTo((byte) 3);\\n        assertThat(slice.getByte(3)).isEqualTo((byte) 6);\\n\\n        slice.setByte(1, 99);\\n        assertThat(buffer.get(3)).isEqualTo((byte) 99);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void directSliceProducesByteBufferBackedBySameMemory() {\\n        Slice slice = Slices.allocateDirect(5);\\n        slice.setBytes(0, new byte[] {10, 11, 12, 13, 14});\\n\\n        ByteBuffer buffer = slice.toByteBuffer();\\n\\n        assertThat(buffer.isDirect()).isTrue();\\n        assertThat(buffer.remaining()).isEqualTo(5);\\n        assertThat(buffer.get(2)).isEqualTo((byte) 12);\\n\\n        buffer.put(3, (byte) 42);\\n        assertThat(slice.getByte(3)).isEqualTo((byte) 42);\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\nhuman-intervention-logs/io.airlift:slice:0.36/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-11T20-05-14-042553Z.log:1757:[tool-call] end id=call_axIcUrLH1yydj00mE3R4fdQq|fc_0b9534823d32c12b016a02361225c8819dac66734657805547 name=write args={\"path\": \"tests/src/io.airlift/slice/0.36/src/test/java/io_airlift/slice/JvmUtilsTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <htt